Author: ddx-checkpoint <checkpoint@ddx.local>
Date:   Mon May 18 00:04:19 2026 -0400

    drop redundant Status==Open filter in Blocked, let EvaluateLifecycleQueue be sole arbiter [ddx-d79228c1]

    EvaluateLifecycleQueue already classifies beads into buckets based on status,
    dependencies, claims, and other lifecycle facts. The redundant Status==StatusOpen
    check in Blocked() violates the principle that the lifecycle module is the
    authoritative classifier for queue buckets.

    This change:
    - Removes the redundant Status==StatusOpen filter from Blocked()
    - Adds a comment explaining that EvaluateLifecycleQueue is the sole arbiter
    - Allows beads with StatusInProgress to be correctly classified as waiting on dependencies

    All call sites tested via 577+ passing unit tests covering lifecycle classification,
    ready/blocked bucket derivation, and dependency-waiting beads.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Haiku 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

